    fn:fold-left(map:keys($B), $A, function($z, $k){ 
        if (map:contains($z, $k))
        then map:put($z, $k, $deduplicator($z($k), $B($k)))
        else map:put($z, $k, $B($k))
    })
}
return fn:fold-left($MAPS, map{}, 
    $combine-maps(?, ?, $duplicates-handler(($OPTIONS?duplicates, "use-first")[1]))

fos:rules.p:
The function map:get attempts to find an entry within the map supplied as $map that has the same key as the supplied
            value of $key. If there is such an entry, it returns the associated value;
            otherwise it returns an empty sequence.

fos:rules.eg:
